  "body": "#### System information\n\nGeth version: tested on `1.4.5-stable` & `1.4.5-stable-a269a713`\nOS & Version: Arch Linux 4.5.4-1\n#### Expected behaviour\n\nI'm using a web3/nodejs script to deploy millions of contracts to a private blockchain. Expected run time is ~2 days to deploy ~50,000000 contracts.\n#### Actual behaviour\n\nAfter approximately 30 mins geth crashes & reviewing geth logs in journalctl I find this:\n\n```\nJun 02 13:28:09 mario geth[9833]: fatal error: concurrent map read and map write\n\nJun 02 13:28:09 mario geth[9833]: goroutine 62878 [running]:\n\nJun 02 13:28:09 mario geth[9833]: runtime.throw(0x1121760, 0x21)\n\nJun 02 13:28:09 mario geth[9833]:         /usr/local/go/src/runtime/panic.go:547 +0x90 fp=0xc82217cda8 sp=0xc82217cd90\n\nJun 02 13:28:09 mario geth[9833]: runtime.mapaccess2(0xcdd980, 0xc8201eafc0, 0xc82217ce18, 0x0, 0x0)\n\nJun 02 13:28:09 mario geth[9833]:         /usr/local/go/src/runtime/hashmap.go:343 +0x5a fp=0xc82217cdf0 sp=0xc82217cda8\n\nJun 02 13:28:09 mario geth[9833]: github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/core.(*TxPool).GetTransaction(0xc8203d65a0, 0xbcd8ed0ca7b3b1f9, 0x852636080acee85c, 0xbe98dd39aa40b0c8, 0x5e76045a7e09d46c, 0x0)\n\nJun 02 13:28:09 mario geth[9833]:         /go/src/github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/build/_workspace/src/github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/core/tx_pool.go:372 +0x5c fp=0xc82217cea0 sp=0xc82217cdf0\n\nJun 02 13:28:09 mario geth[9833]: github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/eth.getTransaction(0x7f86ac256f50, 0xc820430000, 0xc8203d65a0, 0xbcd8ed0ca7b3b1f9, 0x852636080acee85c, 0xbe98dd39aa40b0c8, 0x5e76045a7e09d46c, 0x0, 0xe0e920, 0x0, ...)\n```\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\n\nUsing javascript/web3 and nodejs to deploy contract to a private 1 node network. Single geth instance is receiving the transactions and mining the blocks (difficulty in genesis.json set to 0x4). The contract definition doesn't seem to effect the bug either.\n\n```\nvar numContracts = 50000000;\nvar MyContract = web3.eth.contract(contractAbi);\n\nfor(var i = 0; i < numContracts; i++)\n{\n    var contractInstance = MyContract.new({data: '0x12345...', from: myAccount, gas: 1000000});\n    //optional thread.sleep to spread out transactions, doesn't seem to effect outcome.\n}\n```\n",
